    "problemStatement": "Let **p** be a permutation of integers **1, ..., N**. Lets call **p** good if there is at least one pair of indices **(i,j)** such that **i &lt; j** and **p[i] &gt; j, p[j] &gt; i**.\n\n\n\n**p****1, ..., N****M****i (1 ≤ i ≤ M)****p(Xi)****Vi**\n\n**M****2000000011**",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **T** ≤ **10**",
      "**1** ≤ **N** ≤ **10^9**",
      "**0** ≤ **M** ≤ **10^4**",
      "**1** ≤ **Xi, Vi** ≤ **N**",
      "&nbsp;",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "2",
      "3 0",
      "3 2",
      "3 1",
      "1 2",
      "**Output:**",
      "1",
      "0",
      "&nbsp;",
      "Explanation**Example case 1.** The only good permutation is **3,2,1** (i = 1, j = 2).",
      "Sub tasks",
      "**Subtask #1:** **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **8** (5 points)",
      "**Subtask #2:** **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **20** (10 points)",
      "**Subtask #3:** **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **1000** (15 points)",
      "**Subtask #4:** **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **10000** (15 points)",
      "**Subtask #5:** **1** ≤ **N** ≤ **100000000** (20 points)",
      "**Subtask #6:** **original** (35 points)"
